Key Match Events: Will Smith hit a tying, two-run homer in the seventh inning.
Pages added a two-run, two-strike, two-out homer in the eighth.
Freddie Freeman left the game after colliding with Luis Arráez and the first base bag, grabbing at his lower right leg before hobbling off the field.
Pre-Game Insights: A sellout crowd of 52,433, including retired Dodgers star Manny Ramirez, packed Dodger Stadium for the finale of the crucial series between the top teams in the NL West.
Both teams had already clinched postseason berths.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Dave Roberts said, 'I couldn’t be more proud of these guys. They fought and fought and fought and overcame adversity.'
Roberts also said, 'Doing it in front of the home fans, beating those guys, winning a series, it’s pretty sweet.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers (95-64) had not clinched at home since the pandemic-shortened 2020 season.
The last time fans were on hand for a clincher at home was 2018.
Musgrove threw a heck of a ballgame, you got to tip your hat right there.
The Dodgers got to him in the seventh. Musgrove gave up a leadoff walk to Max Muncy.
Others: RHP Brusdar Graterol went on IL with right shoulder inflammation.
SS Miguel Rojas (left groin tightness) had an MRI that showed a torn adductor. He received a shot and will sit out the next couple days.
LHP Anthony Banda was activated off IL.
Placed RHP Brent Honeywell Jr. on IL with a cracked right middle fingernail.
